#### SUB-SECTION B — Certificate Management via Google Drive (Admin side)

WORKFLOW:
Admin uploads all participant certificates to a designated Google Drive folder.
Each certificate PDF must be named using the student's registered name:
  Format: firstname_lastname.pdf  (e.g., john_doe.pdf, amal_thomas.pdf)

Admin Panel UI:
- Input field: "Google Drive Folder ID or URL" → admin pastes the Drive folder link
- "Sync Certificates" button → triggers the sync process:
    1. Calls Google Drive API to list all files in the specified folder
    2. Parses each filename (strips .pdf, converts underscores to spaces)
    3. Matches each file to a registered participant in the database
       (match by: normalized full name OR fallback to email parsed from filename
        e.g., john_doe@college.edu → john_doe.pdf)
    4. Stores the Google Drive direct download URL for each matched participant:
       Format: https://drive.google.com/uc?export=download&id=<FILE_ID>
    5. Updates participant certificate status in the database

Certificate Status Column in Participants Table:
  - ✅ Available — certificate matched and URL stored
  - ⏳ Review Pending — participant hasn't submitted review yet
  - ❌ Not Uploaded — no matching file found in Drive folder
  - 🔒 Locked — confirmed but review not yet submitted

Admin Controls:
- View sync log: list of matched files, unmatched files, and skipped duplicates
- Re-sync button: re-run the mapping process after uploading new certificates
- Manual override per participant:
    → Paste a direct certificate URL manually for edge cases
    → "Bypass review requirement" checkbox (unlocks certificate without review)
- Duplicate name handling:
    → If two students share the same name, flag as conflict in sync log
    → Admin manually resolves by assigning correct file to each participant

Edge Case Handling (instruct Claude to implement all of these):
- Unmatched files (no student found for that filename) → logged in sync report
- Missing certificates (student exists but no file found) → status = Not Uploaded
- Duplicate filenames in Drive → flagged, admin picks correct one
- Names with special characters or middle names → normalize before matching
  (strip accents, lowercase, trim spaces, ignore middle names as fallback)
- Students who change names after registration → manual URL assignment by admin

Google Drive API Setup Notes (include in code):
- Use Google Drive API v3 with a Service Account (no OAuth popup for admin)
- Store Service Account credentials in environment variables (.env):
    GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_EMAIL=...
    GOOGLE_PRIVATE_KEY=...
    GOOGLE_DRIVE_FOLDER_ID=...
- The Drive folder must be shared with the service account email
- Scope required: https://www.googleapis.com/auth/drive.readonly
- Convert file ID to direct downloadable link:
    https://drive.google.com/uc?export=download&id=<FILE_ID>

